args: ...Finally. That seems to be the last of\nthem for now. I've never seen so many\nfiends.
I went ahead alone to get here as fast as\nI could, but by the look of things...
...Damn. It's as bad as I feared.\nI pray there are at least some survivors...
She still draws breath, but in this cold \nand with a wound like that, I fear the\ngoddess will take her home ere long.
I've already used all my healing power,\nand reinforcements are still far away.\nI can do nothing but offer last rites...
O Ilia, I beseech you beckon forth this\npure soul, that she might find her way\ninto your abundant light.
*pant *pant* D-did I make it in time?
By the goddess, she lives still!\nCan you stabilize her?
Yes, sir! Come on, little one!\nYou can do it!
I think she's going to make it.
If I was able to save even\na single person, then...
Why DID you come back, boy?
I thought you surrendered this dream when\nyou learned you couldn't save everyone.
I didn't want to lie to myself.
I stopped being a knight because it was\ntoo painful, yet I've been suffering that\nsame pain ever since I returned home.
I couldn't stop thinking about it.
That's when I realized that not doing\nanything was the worst pain of all.
You told me I can't save everyone,\nand I know you're right.
But not being able to save people and not\nTRYING to save them are different things!
And I won't ever stop trying!
The person who appeared to me in my\ndreams made me remember that feeling.
He told me nothing good will ever\ncome from surrender.
...And he told you not to lie to your heart.
It was a favorite saying of my own master.\nHe wasn't wise in the slightest, but he\nexcelled in his power to attract people.
Perhaps there's a kind of power possessed\nby those fit to become Heavenwings.

That's enough ruminating on the past, boy.
We should focus on how you remembered
something important, rethought your
position, and returned to the battlefield.
So then? How do you wish to live now as\nyou look out over the battlefield and its\ninexhaustible supply of despair?
I want to become a knight.
It's okay if it's a hard road, or painful.\nNo matter what, I don't want to give\nup on helping people in need.
I'm not going to run away anymore.\nSo please give me one more chance\nto become a knight!
To chase the light even in the midst of\ndarkness is the mark of Ilia's vanguard.\nYou have the heart of a proper knight.

I will reconsider my previous harsh
assessment of your escort missionâ€”
and with that being the case, I would
ask you take up the mantle of Templar.
Templar Hope! Your urgent duty is to find\nand purge all the fiends in this area.\nAre you equal to the task?
I see that young man is back and burning\nwith even greater motivation.
He still lacks proper experience, but his\noutlook has broadened somewhat.
He intends quite earnestly to become a\nHeavenwing, and trains without pause\nin both knightly and priestly arts.
Perhaps there is yet a future where\nhe does not end up a mere pawn.

A lone apprentice can hardly make waves
on their own, but his bladework no longer
shows hesitation. If he can blossom, that
would be an entertaining development...
...Yesss! I've mastered a new technique!\nMaybe now I'm just a little bit closer\nto being like him.
I hope you're watching, wherever you are.
I'm still crawling around in the dirt,\nbut someday I'll soar through the sky!
